                        <p><span class="s1">“Actors need to create distance between themselves and their characters,” Hamilton added. “Transitions between scenes will be very open, nothing will be disguised. I don’t want the audience to forget that they are watching a show.”</span></p>
<p><span class="s1"><i>Urinetown will open in late October. The show runs from the 16</i></span><span class="s2"><i>th</i></span><span class="s1"><i> to the 26</i></span><span class="s2"><i>th</i></span><span class="s1"><i>, in Shaefer Theater. Tickets available through the box office starting Sept. 15</i></span><span class="s2"><i>th</i></span><span class="s1"><i>.</i></span></p>

